    "body": "@mletterle Graydon had a sophisticated plan for how Rust should handle versioning, and the hashes are part of that. They're meant to encode dependencies and not just versions. However, now that Graydon has stepped down from the team, that plan lacks a champion, and we may have to punt on it.\n",
