    "created_at": "2013-11-02T16:28:45Z",
    "updated_at": "2013-11-02T16:28:45Z",
    "body": "Reading the wiki, it looks like the only purpose of the hash is to resolve _soname clashes_. This makes sense, also taking into account the fact that for (far future) system-wide libraries, the soname space is shared also with non-rust libraries.\n\nAs the hash is expected to be static (like the library name and in opposition to the library version/interface signature), I'd like to adopt @metajack proposal: re-use the first group of the crate UUID as the hash. This gives us 8 random alphadigits with a low probability of collision, which are statically defined and known to rustpkg, as well as short and easily greppable. Eg, this will result in a `libhttp-d2ad8df0.so.0.1-pre` for the current httplib version.\n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
